race.comment: RUNAWAY STATEMENT (9) hit the line well last start when finishing fifth over 1400m here just over 3 weeks ago. She is perfectly placed in her third local start since making the move from the mainland, and from the perfect inside draw, she is the one to beat. ZURICH (10) won over 2050m at Hobart nearly 2 weeks ago and will carry no weight here after a 4kg claim from his regular hoop Kirra-Lee Lane. He is only lightly tried and has more to offer. LOVIN' BEV (4) set the pace as usual and ran third as favourite last time out over 1420m on this track, making it four minor placings from five runs this prep. She has finished runner-up in a trial since then and is overdue to win again. TUSKEGEE (5) charged home last start to miss by just a nose over 1600m here 3 weeks ago. That was his first defeat in 4 starts over a mile, and he is right in this. ORIGINAL GLAZE (7) showed good speed to lead throughout and score by a long neck last time here 4 weeks ago. She can hold her form now.
